subSubSection.paragraph:
Gnathopod 2
symmetrical, subchelate; coxa posteroventral corner without notch, ventral margin without robust setae; basis slender, anterodistal corner subquadrate; ischium anterodistal corner without lobes; merus posteroventral corner acute; carpus compressed, length 0.7 × width, anterior margin with 1 slender seta, posterior margin with rows of slender setae;
propodus subovate, length 1.4 × width, posterior margin with clusters of long slender setae, palm length half of propodus posterior margin, angle subacute, distal shelf absent, palm smooth, entire, defined by posteroventral corner with small subacute tooth androbust seta;
dactylus reaching end of and closing along palm, posterior margin smooth, unguis absent.
Pereopods 3–4
coxa subquadrate; basis long, length 3.5 × width; merus, carpus and propodus not broadened; dactylus unguissimple.
